{"title_page": "Carl Sandreczki", "text_new": "{{Underlinked|date=April 2020}}\n\n[[File:Plan der Strassen &amp; Pl\u00e4tze des jetzigen Jerusalem - von Dr. C.Sandreczki.jpg|thumb|Plan der Strassen &amp; Pl\u00e4tze des jetzigen Jerusalem - von Dr. C.Sandreczki]]\n'''Carl Sandreczki''' (1809\u201392) was a German missionary in Palestine in the 19th century.{{sfn| H._Goren|2003|pp=299-302}} He supported the identification of the Arabic names for locations in Jerusalem during the [[Ordnance Survey of Jerusalem]].\n\nHis son, [[Max Sandreczky]], was a paediatric surgeon in Jerusalem.\n\n==Publications==\n*Carl Sandreczki, 'Warren's Ausgrabungen in Jerusalem', PM 14 (1868): p.&nbsp;293-94\n*Carl Sandreczki, 'Briefe aus Palastina', Das Ausland 44 (1871): p.&nbsp;810;\n*Carl Sandreczki, 'Wozu uns Deutscher der \"Palestine Exploration Fund\" ermahnt', Das Ausland 47 (1874): p.&nbsp;114-15.\n*Carl Sandreczki, \u2018Zur alten Geographie Pal\u00e4stina\u2019s\u2019, Das Ausland 5 (1872), p.&nbsp;103\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==References==\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|author=H. Goren|title=\"Zieht hin und erforscht das Land\": die deutsche Pal\u00e4stinaforschung im 19. Jahrhundert [\"Goes and explores the Land\": German research on Palestine in the 19th century]|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wQz1Sg-lhMEC&pg=PA299|year=2003|publisher=Wallstein Verlag|isbn=978-3-89244-673-6}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:German missionaries]]\n[[Category:1808 births]]\n[[Category:1892 deaths]]\n[[Category:Converts to Protestantism from Roman Catholicism]]\n[[Category:German expatriates in the Ottoman Empire]]\n[[Category:Expatriates in Ottoman Palestine]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Plan der Strassen &amp; Pl\u00e4tze des jetzigen Jerusalem - von Dr. C.Sandreczki.jpg|thumb|Plan der Strassen &amp; Pl\u00e4tze des jetzigen Jerusalem - von Dr. C.Sandreczki]]\n'''Carl Sandreczki''' (1809\u201392) was a German missionary in Palestine in the 19th century.{{sfn| H._Goren|2003|pp=299-302}